race.comment: They'll go like the clappers in this. The well-related BREAK FREE (7) (half to G3 winner Snapped) resumes here but has won two from two over this track and trip and is yet to taste defeat in two first-up attempts. Revved up for this with a recent trial win and can run a big race while fresh. OOHLALOUVRE (15) is a consistent conveyance who has placed five of eight over this course and distance and is usually thereabouts. Should give backers a sight. GREYZOUS (9) saves her best form for this sprint journey and will strip fitter second-up from the break. Good enough to feature in the finish. BALTRAY (12) is a two-time winner here who maps nicely from gate three. Keep safe. KAI MONDO (6) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
